## Voice Commands and Speech Recognition

The App offers optional voice command functionality. By using voice features, you acknowledge:

- **Microphone access** is required and requested only when you initiate a voice command or voice check-in
- All audio is processed **on-device** using Apple's Speech Recognition framework
- No audio is recorded, stored, or transmitted to any server
- Audio processing stops immediately when you finish a voice command
- Voice commands are provided as a convenience and may not always be interpreted correctly — always verify the parsed result before confirming

## Co-op Buddies and iCloud

If you use the Co-op Buddies feature:

- An iCloud account is required
- Limited workout summary data (display name, workout completion dates, exercise counts, durations, streak counts, and boss battle contributions) is shared with friends you explicitly invite
- Detailed workout data (specific exercises, weights, reps), daily health logs, and body measurements are **never** shared
- You can remove a buddy or disable the feature at any time, which stops all data sharing
- Co-op data is stored in Apple's CloudKit infrastructure — we do not operate any servers

